Pandas Functions with Examples¶

Function Description Example
head() Show first rows df.head()
tail() Show last rows df.tail()
shape Rows × Columns df.shape
info() Info about dataset df.info()
describe() Summary statistics df.describe()
columns Get column names df.columns
dtypes Data types of columns df.dtypes
isnull() Check missing values df.isnull().sum()
dropna() Remove missing values df.dropna()
fillna() Fill missing values df.fillna(0)
sort_values() Sort dataset df.sort_values('Age')
groupby() Group data df.groupby('Age')['Marks'].mean()
value_counts() Count unique values df['Age'].value_counts()
unique() Unique values df['Name'].unique()
nunique() Number of unique values df['Name'].nunique()
Description Code Example Explanation
Select a column df['price'] Selects the price column
Select multiple columns df[['airline','price']] Selects multiple columns
Select row by index df.loc[0] First row by index label
Select row by position df.iloc[0] First row by integer position
Filter rows (condition) df[df['price'] > 5000] Selects rows where price > 5000
Multiple conditions df[(df['price'] > 5000) & (df['airline'] == 'Vistara')] Rows where price > 5000 AND airline is Vistara
Select specific rows & cols df.loc[0:5, ['airline','price']] Rows 0–5 with selected columns
Add new column df['discounted_price'] = df['price'] * 0.9 Creates a new column with 10% discount
Modify column values df['price'] = df['price'] + 100 Increases all prices by 100
Drop column df.drop('days_left', axis=1) Removes days_left column
Drop row df.drop(0, axis=0) Removes row with index 0
Sort values df.sort_values('price', ascending=False) Sort by price descending
Rename column df.rename(columns={'price':'ticket_price'}, inplace=True) Renames column price → ticket_price

Image Data Preprocessing

1. BAR GRAPH - number of detected diseases by Age¶

In [53]:
df.groupby("age")["heart_disease"].value_counts().unstack().plot(
    kind="bar", figsize=(8,5)
)
plt.title("Disease Detection by Age")
plt.ylabel("Number of Patients")
plt.show()

  • Works well with big datasets

  • Connects with other Python libraries
  • Is widely used in Data Science, AI, and Business Analytics
